cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with pedestrian detection using multi-modal sensors. The use of deep neural networks for segmentation and supervised learning also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The focus on real-time applications and autonomous driving suggests that it could also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the use of multispectral sensors suggests that it could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
